      {
        "id": "c25a574bfa5a063ac0f8c37c25d89429f03f6f20",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2789,
          "name": "Lukasz Muszkieta",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "lukasz.muszkieta@nokia.com",
          "username": "lukaszM"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-10-22 16:55:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review-2\n\nThis is not the solution of this problem.\n\nThe problem is that we get the list of orchestation flows sorted by primary id, not by sequenceNumber.\nSequenceNumber defines the order of building block execution.\n\nThe problem appears after the following commit:\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/so/+/111019\n\nAfter inserting the ControllerExecutionBB into table, it is on the last record of the table orchestation_flow_reference. \n\nAnd that is why when we get the list of bb in WorkflowAction class, ControllerExecutionBB is the last,\nbut it can not be the last, it must be executed after waitForPnfBB, because this is defined by sequence number.\n\nHere is a solution corrected by me, it is tested on lab and works.\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/so/+/114127",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "4570074d471f20207acab15802d0eef571eaffaf",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3543,
          "name": "Sharan Kalkere Ramesh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sk720x@att.com",
          "username": "sharanKR2018"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-10-22 17:05:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> Patch Set 5: Code-Review-2\n> \n> This is not the solution of this problem.\n> \n> The problem is that we get the list of orchestation flows sorted by primary id, not by sequenceNumber.\n> SequenceNumber defines the order of building block execution.\n> \n> The problem appears after the following commit:\n> https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/so/+/111019\n> \n> After inserting the ControllerExecutionBB into table, it is on the last record of the table orchestation_flow_reference. \n> \n> And that is why when we get the list of bb in WorkflowAction class, ControllerExecutionBB is the last,\n> but it can not be the last, it must be executed after waitForPnfBB, because this is defined by sequence number.\n> \n> Here is a solution corrected by me, it is tested on lab and works.\n> https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/so/+/114127\n\nI think both solutions are needed as we need to have a check in place to make sure we don't go out of bounds even if we assume ControllerExecutionBB will not be the last BB. Also the Listener should be called in a separate task for clarity as it updating the flow. Also this change is needed as, future flow manipulators might not have the same assumption that SkipCDSBuildingBlockListener has.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
